> Turn key and starter spins slowly (maybe 2 turns per
> second) and gets slower until it stops turning
> altogether. <<

Could also be a bad ground. Check that the tranny to
chassis ground strap is connected and not chewed. Or
even easier, run a jumper cable from the negative
battery post and attach it to the engine case
(somewhere AWAY from the fuel pump and carb).


